---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---
<BaseLayout title="BridgeAIChat Claude Guide" description="Configure Claude CLI as a BridgeAIChat tool with direct mode for reliable responses.">
  <section class="surface">
    <div class="eyebrow">Tool Guide</div>
    <h1>Claude is a first-class tool — set <code>direct: true</code>.</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      Claude CLI works well with BridgeAIChat. The one required config flag is <code>direct: true</code>, which
      runs Claude as a direct subprocess and captures stdout — bypassing tmux pane scanning, which breaks for
      short responses.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section-gap grid two">
    <div class="card stack">
      <div class="eyebrow">Recommended config</div>
      <h2>Minimal Claude block</h2>
      <pre>tools:
  claude:
    cmd: claude
    args: ["-p", "--dangerously-skip-permissions"]
    continue_args: ["--continue", "-p", "--dangerously-skip-permissions"]
    direct: true

default_tool: claude</pre>
      <p><code>direct: true</code> runs Claude as a subprocess and returns its stdout. <code>--dangerously-skip-permissions</code> bypasses interactive tool permission prompts — without it, Claude will block indefinitely waiting for stdin that never arrives. Conversation context is preserved via Claude's built-in <code>--continue</code> flag.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card stack">
      <div class="eyebrow">Why direct: true</div>
      <h2>What it fixes</h2>
      <ul class="list tight">
        <li>The tmux pane-scanning path tracks new content by row count. A 24-row pane with a short response never grows in row count — the sentinel is never detected and responses time out.</li>
        <li><code>direct: true</code> runs <code>claude -p "…"</code> as a subprocess, captures stdout when it exits, and streams it back. No pane scanning, no sentinel.</li>
        <li>Follow-up turns use <code>continue_args: ["--continue", "-p"]</code> automatically — conversation context is preserved through Claude's own session state.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-gap grid two">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="eyebrow">Before you test</div>
      <h2>Verify the local device</h2>
      <pre>claude -p "hi"</pre>
      <p>If that command fails on the agent device directly, BridgeAIChat cannot fix it. Check login state and quota first.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <div class="eyebrow">Common blockers</div>
      <h2>What usually goes wrong</h2>
      <ul class="list tight">
        <li>Missing <code>direct: true</code> — responses silently time out</li>
        <li>Missing <code>--dangerously-skip-permissions</code> — Claude blocks on a permission prompt with no stdin to answer it; you see Claude's "grant permission" message instead of a real reply</li>
        <li>The device is not logged into Claude CLI</li>
        <li>Hourly or daily quota exhausted on the account</li>
        <li>The configured <code>cmd</code> path does not match the installed Claude binary</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
